<div id="quick-start" class="mb-20">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Quick Start</h2>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-6">
            <div class="font-mono text-sm space-y-6">
                <div>
                    <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mb-2">
                        1. Create an R2 bucket + S3 API token in the Cloudflare dashboard
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-zinc-950 rounded p-3 text-zinc-300">
                        <a
                            href="https://dash.cloudflare.com"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-amber-400 hover:underline"
                        >
                            dash.cloudflare.com
                        </a>
                        <span class="text-zinc-500"> -> R2 Object Storage -> Create bucket -> API Tokens</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-zinc-500 text-xs mt-2">
                        You need the Access Key ID, Secret Access Key, Account ID, and bucket name.
                        <a href="/docs#setup" class="text-amber-400 hover:underline">See detailed instructions.</a>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mb-2">
                        2. Deploy the worker
                    </div>
                    <pre class="bg-zinc-950 rounded p-3 overflow-x-auto text-zinc-300"><code>cd packages/worker
bash setup.sh</code></pre>
                    <p class="text-zinc-500 text-xs mt-2">
                        Creates D1 database, sets secrets (including R2 credentials), and deploys.
                        Outputs a worker URL and auth token.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mb-2">
                        3. Install the CLI
                    </div>
                    <pre class="bg-zinc-950 rounded p-3 overflow-x-auto text-zinc-300"><code>npm install -g residue</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mb-2">
                        4. Login, init, and set up an adapter
                    </div>
                    <pre class="bg-zinc-950 rounded p-3 overflow-x-auto text-zinc-300"><code>residue login --url https://your-worker.workers.dev --token YOUR_TOKEN
cd your-project
residue init
residue setup claude-code   <span class="text-zinc-500"># or: residue setup pi</span></code></pre>
                    <p class="text-zinc-500 text-xs mt-2">
                        Installs git hooks and configures your agent adapter.
                        Commit and push as usual -- conversations are captured automatically.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
